- RLS : `ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`, policy SELECT ouverte à tous (`USING (true)`).

- Table `shop_purchases` (ledger des achats, symétrique de wallet_transactions pour les gains) :
  - `id uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()`
  - `user_id uuid NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE`
  - `shop_item_id uuid NOT NULL REFERENCES shop_items(id)`
  - `price_paid int NOT NULL CHECK (price_paid > 0)`
  - `created_at timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now()`
  - Index sur `(user_id, created_at DESC)`
  - RLS : SELECT own uniquement.

- RPC `purchase_item(p_shop_item_id uuid) RETURNS jsonb` :
  - `LANGUAGE plpgsql SECURITY DEFINER SET search_path = public`
  - Vérifie `auth.uid()` non null (sinon `RAISE EXCEPTION 'not_authenticated'`)
  - Load la ligne shop_items (sinon `'item_not_found'`)
  - Fenêtre de disponibilité : `now() < available_from` → `'not_yet_available'` ; `now() > available_until` → `'no_longer_available'`
  - Check non déjà possédé dans `user_inventory` → `'already_owned'`
  - Check balance suffisante (`SELECT balance FROM user_wallet`) → `'insufficient_balance'` sinon
  - UPDATE atomique : `UPDATE user_wallet SET balance = balance - price, updated_at = now() WHERE user_id = v_user_id AND balance >= price RETURNING balance INTO v_new_balance` (protège contre race condition) ; si 0 row → `'insufficient_balance'`
  - INSERT dans `shop_purchases (user_id, shop_item_id, price_paid)`
  - INSERT dans `user_inventory (user_id, item_type, item_id, source)` avec `source='shop'` ; ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING
  - RETURN `jsonb_build_object('balance', v_new_balance, 'item_type', v_item.item_type, 'item_id', v_item.item_id)`
  - `REVOKE ALL FROM public, anon; GRANT EXECUTE TO authenticated;`

